Question: Many universities require that freshman live on campus dorm during the first year of college. In your opinion, is this a good or a bad thing? Explain your opinion on this issue.
Answer:
I think it is a good thing to make freshmen live on campus their freshman year of college. Being with a group of people your age and not related to you is a novel experience people shouldn't miss out on. I've heard some graduates desribe how the best friends they made from college were who they met their freshman year. I think you lose out on that if you live somewhere else than a college dorm.